full_text: Log in as an underwriter Alice Applegate. Open a bound policy. The policy is effective from January 1 to July 1. A policy period is a version of the policy. Each policy job has a selected policy period associated with it. The F dated entities in the policy period keep their state over the effective time of a policy. Start a new policy change. The policy change is effective on March 1, which is after the policy term start date. Change some values on the policy. For example, go to Vehicles. Change the car's color from red to blue. Quote the policy. Issue policy. Click OK. Click OK. Go back to the policy. Click Actions. Start a second policy change. Set the effective date to be after the previous job, for example, May 1. Go to Vehicles. Change the same car's color to a different value.
